<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,265,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="451">Mantispa</emphasis>
Illiger, 
<number box="[361,420,1878,1904]" pageId="50" pageNumber="451" value="1798.0">1798</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,1949,2010]" lastBlockId="51.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="452" pageId="50" pageNumber="451">
Hoffman (
<number box="[269,329,1950,1974]" pageId="50" pageNumber="451" value="1992.0">1992</number>
), proposed a new classification which divides 
<taxonomicName box="[868,974,1950,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Mantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[868,974,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="451">Mantispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in various genera in his revision on the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,290,1985,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Mantispinae">Mantispinae</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[329,429,1985,2010]" name="United States of America" pageId="50" pageNumber="451">America</collectingCountry>
. The author’s study was based on the species groups in the review of Penny &amp; da 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="452" pageId="50" pageNumber="451" refString="Penny, N. D. &amp; da Costa, C. A. (1983) Mantispideos do Brasil (Neuroptera: Mantispidae). Acta Amazonica, 13 (3 - 4), 601 - 687." type="journal article" year="1983">
Costa (
<number box="[159,220,152,176]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Consequently 
<taxonomicName box="[423,529,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Mantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[423,529,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">Mantispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted only to the Old World. Thus, the 
<taxonomicName box="[1156,1242,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Dicromantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1156,1242,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, became 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 2002" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,507,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Dicromantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,318,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">Dicromantispa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman" box="[329,507,188,213]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">
Hoffman, 
<number box="[448,507,188,212]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<taxonomicName box="[568,646,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Zeugomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[568,646,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, was divided into genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 2002" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2002" box="[1031,1384,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Leptomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1198,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">Leptomantispa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman" box="[1209,1384,188,213]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">
Hoffman, 
<number box="[1328,1384,188,212]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 2002" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,504,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Zeugomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,324,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">Zeugomantispa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman" box="[331,504,223,248]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">
Hoffman, 
<number box="[445,504,224,248]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and the 
<taxonomicName box="[605,708,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phthisica">
<emphasis box="[605,708,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">phthisica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is now referred to as the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Navas, 1926" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1926" box="[1139,1361,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Buyda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1139,1211,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">Buyda</emphasis>
Navás, 
<number box="[1302,1361,223,248]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" value="1926.0">1926</number>
</taxonomicName>
. Other genera were proposed for species that could not be assigned to any of the above, as in the case of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 2002" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Haematomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1230,1436,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">Haematomantispa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman" box="[151,321,295,320]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">
Hoffman, 
<number box="[265,321,296,320]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hoffman, 2002" authorityName="Hoffman" authorityYear="2002" box="[376,713,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Xeromantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[376,532,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="452">Xeromantispa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman" box="[539,713,295,320]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" refString="Hoffman, K. M. (2002) Family Mantispidae. In Penny, N. D. (ed.), A guide to the lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (12), 251 - 275." type="journal article" year="2002">
Hoffman, 
<number box="[653,713,296,320]" pageId="51" pageNumber="452" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
